8 Dec 2015 The Deputy Minister of Communications Stella Ndabeni Abrahams to deliver The Keynote address at the International Institute of Communications (IIC)Telecommunication and Media Forum on The 9 December 2015 at 08h30 at the Radison Hotel in Sandton, GautengThe Deputy Minister of Communications, Hon. Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams (MP) will participate in the conference on the 8th and deliver a key note address on the 9th Dec 2015 at the International Institute of Communications (IIC) Telecommunications and Media Forum to be hosted by the Independent Communications Authority of South Africa (ICASA) on 08-09 December 2015 in Johannesburg, Gauteng.The IIC Telecommunications and Media Forum (TMF) programme serves to enhance the telecommunications, media and technology sector's knowledge and understanding of emerging policy and technologies on a fast-track basis. It is the policymaking world's only continuous programme of its kind.Details are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 09 December 2015 Time: 08h30 Venue: Radisson Blue Hotel, SandtonEnquires: Mzimasi Ngqelu Contact: 076 904 3557 Email: mzi@doc.gov.za Issued by Government Communications (GCIS) on behalf of the Ministry of Communications